item.description: 4. Rimac Nevera While electric cars are known for instant acceleration due to their electric motors, battery weight often hinders top speed. However, this car defies this trend. This hypercar boasts four electric motors, generating a remarkable 1,914hp and 2,300Nm of torque. With this power, it accelerates from 0-60mph in just 1.9 seconds and can reach a top speed of 258mph. Its carbon fiber construction keeps weight in check, and despite its incredible performance, it offers a luxurious interior, making it a well-rounded option for those willing to invest in its £2 million price tag.
